# Performance

Adaptron sits in front of LLM agents. Wrapping, port checks, and adapters must add negligible latency (`PRD.md` §7).

## Do

- Keep adapter registry as `dict[tuple[type, type], Callable]` — O(1) exact lookup.
- Reuse stage lists; flatten pipelines without deep recursion when chaining many stages.
- Truncate log previews; never dump large payloads by default.
- Lazy-import optional frameworks so `import adaptron` stays cheap.

## Do not

- Walk MRO / try multiple adapters per connection in v1 (out of scope and slower / ambiguous).
- Allocate heavy temporary structures in the `run()` loop.
- Add caching layers, thread pools, or async runtimes “for performance” without a measured need.
- Optimize prematurely — profile only if overhead is measurable against typical LLM call times.
